'''Cowbellpedia Secondary Schools Mathematics TV Quiz Show''' is a Nigerian national mathematics television [[quiz show]] that debuted in 2015. It showcases young mathematical minds in Nigeria on cable TV [[Africa Magic]] Family channel 154.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2017/01/cowbellpedia-search-best-student-begins-2017-maths-quiz-opens/|title=COWBELLPEDIA : Search for best student begins as 2017 Maths quiz opens – Vanguard News|date=2017-01-19|work=Vanguard News|access-date=2018-10-08|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2018/01/impact-students-mathematics-20-years-cowbellpedia/|title=Our impact on students’ Mathematics for 20 years — Cowbellpedia – Vanguard News|date=2018-01-25|work=Vanguard News|access-date=2018-10-08|language=en-US}}</ref>

This competition sees six students each representing their school compete in an episode where two qualifies and four of them are eliminated in two difficult rounds with three increasingly difficult levels. The winners of the competition in the two categories receives the award of the Next Future Inventor. 

A season of the show is made up of sixteen episodes in which there is a special episode dedicated to the teachers where the best teacher of the year emerges.

== History ==
The initiative began in 1998 as Cowbell National Secondary School Mathematics Competition (NASSMAC) when it was a written examination without a TV show. The name comes from a milk brand (Cowbell, Our Milk) that sponsors the competition.<ref name="auto">{{cite web|url=https://www.hotnigerianjobs.com/hotjobs/80840/2016-cowbell-national-secondary-schools-mathematic.html|title=Cowbell National Secondary Schools Mathematics Competition 2016|first=|last=Hotnigerianjobs|website=Hot Nigerian Jobs}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://takenotenigeria.com/2015/07/21/list-winners-cowbell-national-secondary-schools-mathematics-competition/|title=Cowbell National Mathematics Competition- List of Winners for Junior and Senior Categories – Take Note Nigeria|date=21 July 2015|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://punchng.com/winners-emerge-in-cowbellpedia-mathematics-competition/|title=Winners emerge in Cowbellpedia Mathematics Competition|publisher=}}</ref>

In 2015, the initiative took a new dimension where it’s split into two stages. The stage one is the Qualifying Written Examination and the Stage two is the TV quiz competition.<ref name="auto"/>  The top prize was increased to 2 million Nigerian Naira in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://guardian.ng/features/education/qualifying-exam-for-2018-cowbellpedia-mathematics-competition-holds-february-17/|title=Qualifying exam for 2018 Cowbellpedia Mathematics Competition holds February 17|publisher=}}</ref>

